title: For Sale:  Marlin Model 60 22LR
postcontent:
Marlin 60

Marlin 60 22LR with last shot hold-open. I bought this rifle about 2 months ago for a rapid fire plinker. The seller had a few available as he apparently refurbishes Marlin 60s as a hobby. Of the three he had available, one was outfitted with a scope. Since I had planned on an optic anyway, I selected the scoped offering. The scope is a very basic Bushnell 4X, but perfect for a 22 plinker. The rifle proved to be very accurate and reliable with both CCI mini-mag and Lapua match ammo. Upon removing the scope I discovered that the barrel is rotated to the left by about 5 degrees. I contacted the seller and received an explanation of why it was so, but no apology and no offer to rectify the matter. Clearly, there was a reason that rifle was offered with a scope already mounted! Caveat emptor.

I believe in full disclosure. So, here it is:

Marlin Model 60
15+(?) tubular magazine
Last shot hold-open
light marks on stock with a couple of minor scratches
Metal is in generally good shape with freckling on the barrel and receiver
Bushnell 4X scope and rings
Custom, 5-degree (or so) counter-clockwise barrel rotation

The rifle functions as it should, and the flaw with the barrel is not obvious unless you are attempting to use the iron sights. My problem with the rifle is that it reminds me that I got screwed every time I look at it. I paid $170. I will sell the rifle and the scope for $125 or best offer.

I live in Poulsbo, so I would be willing to travel as far as the ferry terminal at Bainbridge or Kingston. Valid Washington ID required for purchase. More pictures are available upon request.

Thanks for reading.

title: For Sale/Trade:  FN Custom Built Rifle
location: Rocky Mount, NC, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
I have a one of a kind rifle for sale or trade. I was fortunate enough to be able to acquire a custom built FN Sniper Rifle chambered in .308. This rifle was built by FN in the 90s for the West Virginia State Police. A total of three were made and this happens to be one of them. The rifle features a beautifully blued and blueprinted FN mauser action made in Belgium with the serial number A102. The trigger is made by FN and is set at 2lbs. title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson 547
postcontent:
Looks like new, with original bill of sales, all papers and original box, not looking for offers, would consider trade on a 44 3" s&w revolver with fixed sights;
    This is a heavy barrel, 9mm (9x19) version of the legendary K-frame, 6-shot M&P revolver. S&W made 10,270 of these from 1980-1985; 6486 round with butt (and 3" barrel), and 3784 with a square butt and 4" barrel (one listed). Supposedly, this was the most difficult-to-manufacture revolver that S&W ever made.
 In the late 1970's, the Israelis wanted to arm the Palestinian Police force with a 9mm handgun, but didn't trust them with an auto loading pistol. Instead, they wanted a simple-to-use a revolver chambered in 9mm (and by "simple-to-use", they meant "no-moon-clips"). They contracted with Smith & Wesson to make it for them. Instead of the usual "star" type extractor, the Model 547 features a horn-shaped extractor with small beryllium-copper spring tabs that grab the rim of each case.
 Soon after Smith & Wesson delivered the first shipment of these revolvers, the Israeli government cancelled the rest of the order and instead bought an IMI revolver that was a Model 547 knockoff. S&W released the remaining guns to the civilian market, and ended production due to extremely high manufacturing costs.  Consider trade on a S&W 44 mag with short barrel 4" & under.
